      "source": [
        "# **CENSUS INCOME PREDICTION**\n",
        "\n",
        "*   The economic well-being of a Nation is highly driven by the income of the residence.\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "![Screenshot 2024-02-12 173334.png](data:image/png;base64,)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "EWUMEFHyO-Ua"
      },
      "source": [
        "ABOUT THE DATASET\n",
        "\n",
        "The dataset provided to us contains 48842 rows and 14 different independent features. We aim to predict if a person earns more than 50K$ per year or not. Since the data predicts 2 values (>50K or <=50K), this clearly is a classification problem, and we will train the classification models to predict the desired outputs.\n",
        "\n",
        "Mentioned below are the details of the features provided to us, which we will be feeding to our classification model to train it.\n",
        "\n",
        "1.   Age : The age of an individual, this ranges from 17 to 90.\n",
        "2.   Workclass : The class of work to which an individual belongs.\n",
        "3.   Fnlwgt : The weight assigned to the combination of features (an estimate of how many people belong to this set of combination).\n",
        "4.   Education : Highest level of education.\n",
        "5.   Education-num : Number of years for which education was taken.\n",
        "6.   Marital-status : Represents the category assigned on the basis of marriage status of a person.\n",
        "7.   Occupation : Profession of a person.\n",
        "8.   Relationship : Relation of the person in his family.\n",
        "9.   Race : Origin background of a person.\n",
        "10.  Gender : Gender of a person.\n",
        "11.  Capital-gain : Capital gained by a person.\n",
        "12.  Capital-loss : Loss of capital for a person.\n",
        "13.  Hours-per-week : Number of hours for which an individual works per week.\n",
        "14.  Native-country : Country to which a person belongs.\n",
        "\n",
        "Output:\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "1.   Income : The target variable, which predicts if the income is higher or lower than 50K\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "9G-IkG7xY3re"
      },
      "source": [

              "\n",
              "      async function convertToInteractive(key) {\n",
              "        const element = document.querySelector('#df-707bc752-35cf-4dcf-88d4-7d8a1d72d94a');\n",
              "        const dataTable =\n",
              "          await google.colab.kernel.invokeFunction('convertToInteractive',\n",
              "                                                    [key], {});\n",
              "        if (!dataTable) return;\n",
              "\n",
              "        const docLinkHtml = 'Like what you see? Visit the ' +\n",
              "          '<a target=\"_blank\" href=https://colab.research.google.com/notebooks/data_table.ipynb>data table notebook</a>'\n",
              "          + ' to learn more about interactive tables.';\n",
              "        element.innerHTML = '';\n",
              "        dataTable['output_type'] = 'display_data';\n",
              "        await google.colab.output.renderOutput(dataTable, element);\n",
              "        const docLink = document.createElement('div');\n",
              "        docLink.innerHTML = docLinkHtml;\n",
              "        element.appendChild(docLink);\n",
              "      }\n",
              "    </script>\n",

              "      async function convertToInteractive(key) {\n",
              "        const element = document.querySelector('#df-4b053d12-57f5-42fd-948f-7cf4d0c5a6c7');\n",
              "        const dataTable =\n",
              "          await google.colab.kernel.invokeFunction('convertToInteractive',\n",
              "                                                    [key], {});\n",
              "        if (!dataTable) return;\n",
              "\n",
              "        const docLinkHtml = 'Like what you see? Visit the ' +\n",
              "          '<a target=\"_blank\" href=https://colab.research.google.com/notebooks/data_table.ipynb>data table notebook</a>'\n",
              "          + ' to learn more about interactive tables.';\n",
              "        element.innerHTML = '';\n",
              "        dataTable['output_type'] = 'display_data';\n",
              "        await google.colab.output.renderOutput(dataTable, element);\n",
              "        const docLink = document.createElement('div');\n",
              "        docLink.innerHTML = docLinkHtml;\n",
              "        element.appendChild(docLink);\n",
              "      }\n",
              "    </script>\n",
              "  </div>\n",

              "      async function convertToInteractive(key) {\n",
              "        const element = document.querySelector('#df-2cfaa0b4-5e48-470f-9dfd-0072cfff0097');\n",
              "        const dataTable =\n",
              "          await google.colab.kernel.invokeFunction('convertToInteractive',\n",
              "                                                    [key], {});\n",
              "        if (!dataTable) return;\n",
              "\n",
              "        const docLinkHtml = 'Like what you see? Visit the ' +\n",
              "          '<a target=\"_blank\" href=https://colab.research.google.com/notebooks/data_table.ipynb>data table notebook</a>'\n",
              "          + ' to learn more about interactive tables.';\n",
              "        element.innerHTML = '';\n",
              "        dataTable['output_type'] = 'display_data';\n",
              "        await google.colab.output.renderOutput(dataTable, element);\n",
              "        const docLink = document.createElement('div');\n",
              "        docLink.innerHTML = docLinkHtml;\n",
              "        element.appendChild(docLink);\n",
              "      }\n",
              "    </script>\n",
              "  </div>\n",

              "      async function convertToInteractive(key) {\n",
              "        const element = document.querySelector('#df-d32ae5b2-0e3b-49fb-be1a-750777a7a2b0');\n",
              "        const dataTable =\n",
              "          await google.colab.kernel.invokeFunction('convertToInteractive',\n",
              "                                                    [key], {});\n",
              "        if (!dataTable) return;\n",
              "\n",
              "        const docLinkHtml = 'Like what you see? Visit the ' +\n",
              "          '<a target=\"_blank\" href=https://colab.research.google.com/notebooks/data_table.ipynb>data table notebook</a>'\n",
              "          + ' to learn more about interactive tables.';\n",
              "        element.innerHTML = '';\n",
              "        dataTable['output_type'] = 'display_data';\n",
              "        await google.colab.output.renderOutput(dataTable, element);\n",
              "        const docLink = document.createElement('div');\n",
              "        docLink.innerHTML = docLinkHtml;\n",
              "        element.appendChild(docLink);\n",
              "      }\n",
              "    </script>\n",

      "source": [
        "MISSING VALUE HANDLING"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "l1pKFPY39fdn",
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "outputId": "f896760d-bb06-417d-8b1e-3f4ff7c4805f"
      },
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "execute_result",
          "data": {
            "text/plain": [
              "age                0\n",
              "workclass          0\n",
              "fnlwgt             0\n",
              "education          0\n",
              "educational-num    0\n",
              "marital-status     0\n",
              "occupation         0\n",
              "relationship       0\n",
              "race               0\n",
              "gender             0\n",
              "capital-gain       0\n",
              "capital-loss       0\n",
              "hours-per-week     0\n",
              "native-country     0\n",
              "income             0\n",
              "dtype: int64"
            ]
          },
          "metadata": {},
          "execution_count": 32
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "df['workclass']=df['workclass'].fillna(df['workclass'].mode()[0])\n",
        "df['occupation']=df['occupation'].fillna(df['occupation'].mode()[0])\n",
        "df['native-country']=df['native-country'].fillna(df['native-country'].mode()[0])\n",
        "df.isna().sum()"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "1AX_KI547o23"
      },
      "source": [
        "LABEL ENCODING"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "bPmfX7Z7wQ1Y",
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"

      },

              "      async function convertToInteractive(key) {\n",
              "        const element = document.querySelector('#df-0f40e79c-1c5b-4cd7-9006-b4998f93afbd');\n",

              "      async function convertToInteractive(key) {\n",
              "        const element = document.querySelector('#df-0fa99922-7b4c-4783-859b-54d343307825');\n",
              "        const dataTable =\n",
              "          await google.colab.kernel.invokeFunction('convertToInteractive',\n",
              "                                                    [key], {});\n",
              "        if (!dataTable) return;\n",
              "\n",
              "        const docLinkHtml = 'Like what you see? Visit the ' +\n",
              "          '<a target=\"_blank\" href=https://colab.research.google.com/notebooks/data_table.ipynb>data table notebook</a>'\n",
              "          + ' to learn more about interactive tables.';\n",
              "        element.innerHTML = '';\n",
              "        dataTable['output_type'] = 'display_data';\n",
              "        await google.colab.output.renderOutput(dataTable, element);\n",
              "        const docLink = document.createElement('div');\n",
              "        docLink.innerHTML = docLinkHtml;\n",
              "        element.appendChild(docLink);\n",
              "      }\n",
              "    </script>\n",

              "      async function convertToInteractive(key) {\n",
              "        const element = document.querySelector('#df-1add6b62-039f-4a43-99c7-9df0cfcf701b');\n",
              "        const dataTable =\n",
              "          await google.colab.kernel.invokeFunction('convertToInteractive',\n",
              "                                                    [key], {});\n",
              "        if (!dataTable) return;\n",
              "\n",
              "        const docLinkHtml = 'Like what you see? Visit the ' +\n",
              "          '<a target=\"_blank\" href=https://colab.research.google.com/notebooks/data_table.ipynb>data table notebook</a>'\n",
              "          + ' to learn more about interactive tables.';\n",
              "        element.innerHTML = '';\n",
              "        dataTable['output_type'] = 'display_data';\n",
              "        await google.colab.output.renderOutput(dataTable, element);\n",
              "        const docLink = document.createElement('div');\n",
              "        docLink.innerHTML = docLinkHtml;\n",
              "        element.appendChild(docLink);\n",
              "      }\n",

      "source": [
        "OUTLIER DETECTION AND REMOVAL"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "ePzHQ-QyKyHP"
      },
      "source": [
        "OUTLIER : A data point that significantly differs from other observations in a dataset.\n",
        "\n",
        "IQR (Inter Quartile Range)\n",
        "\n",
        "IQR = Q3-Q1\n",
        "\n",
        "Maximum outlier(top) = Q3+1.5*IQR\n",
        "\n",
        "Minimum outlier(bottom) = Q1-1.5*IQR"
      ]
    },

              "      async function convertToInteractive(key) {\n",
              "        const element = document.querySelector('#df-61624b54-8849-495e-9bf3-a429625895cb');\n",
              "        const dataTable =\n",
              "          await google.colab.kernel.invokeFunction('convertToInteractive',\n",
              "                                                    [key], {});\n",
              "        if (!dataTable) return;\n",
              "\n",
              "        const docLinkHtml = 'Like what you see? Visit the ' +\n",
              "          '<a target=\"_blank\" href=https://colab.research.google.com/notebooks/data_table.ipynb>data table notebook</a>'\n",
              "          + ' to learn more about interactive tables.';\n",
              "        element.innerHTML = '';\n",
              "        dataTable['output_type'] = 'display_data';\n",
              "        await google.colab.output.renderOutput(dataTable, element);\n",
              "        const docLink = document.createElement('div');\n",
              "        docLink.innerHTML = docLinkHtml;\n",
              "        element.appendChild(docLink);\n",
              "      }\n",
              "    </script>\n",
              "  </div>\n",

        "from sklearn.neighbors import KNeighborsClassifier\n",
        "from sklearn.naive_bayes import BernoulliNB\n",
        "from sklearn.svm import SVC\n",
        "from sklearn.tree import DecisionTreeClassifier\n",
        "from sklearn.metrics import confusion_matrix,accuracy_score,classification_report,ConfusionMatrixDisplay\n",
        "knn_model=KNeighborsClassifier(n_neighbors=7,weights='distance')\n",
        "naive_model=BernoulliNB()\n",
        "svm_model=SVC()\n",
        "tree_model=DecisionTreeClassifier(criterion='entropy')\n",
        "lst_model=[knn_model,naive_model,svm_model,tree_model]"
      ]
    },

        "label=['>50K','<=50K']\n",
        "for i in lst_model:\n",
        "  print(\"Model name is\",i)\n",
        "  i.fit(x_train,y_train)\n",
        "  y_pred=i.predict(x_test)\n",
        "  print(\"Confusion matrix\")\n",
        "  mat=confusion_matrix(y_test,y_pred)\n",
        "  print(mat)\n",
        "  print(\"Accuracy score\")\n",
        "  print(accuracy_score(y_test,y_pred))\n",
        "  print(classification_report(y_test,y_pred))\n",
        "  dis=ConfusionMatrixDisplay(mat,display_labels=label)\n",
        "  dis.plot()\n",
        "  print(\"*\"*100)"
      ]
